the Earn product was safe and liquid, and that it did good due diligence on=
 Genesis to make sure that the loans were safe:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From February 9, 2021, through at =
least November 14, 2022, Gemini referred to Genesis Capital on the Earn Pag=
e as a =E2=80=9Ctrusted partner[]=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Caccredited third pa=
rty borrower[]=E2=80=9D that Gemini =E2=80=9Cvetted through a risk manageme=
nt framework which reviews [Genesis Capital=E2=80=99s] collateralization ma=
nagement process.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Specifically, it advertised that the loans wer=
e =E2=80=9Covercollateralized,=E2=80=9D that when Genesis loaned out $100 w=
orth of Gemini customers=E2=80=99 crypto it got back collateral worth at le=
ast $101:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On February 2, 2021, Gemini=E2=80=
=99s Head of Risk stated in a press release that, =E2=80=9CGemini reviewed =
Genesis [Capital=E2=80=99s] financial statements and verified that the lend=
er=E2=80=99s loans are overcollateralized.=E2=80=9D Overcollateralization m=
eans that the collateral supporting outstanding loans is worth more than 10=
0% of those loans.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But =E2=80=9Ccontrary to Gemini=E2=80=99s clai=
m, Genesis Capital=E2=80=99s loan book was not overcollateralized, either w=
hen Gemini claimed it was or at any time thereafter=E2=80=9D; collateral co=
verage ranged from about 60% to about 90% of loan value over 2020 through 2=
022. And:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gemini internally acknowledged thi=
s misrepresentation. On March 9, 2021, a risk management employee reporting=
 directly to Gemini=E2=80=99s Head of Risk corrected a similar misstatement=
 by stating: =E2=80=9C[l]ending is =E2=80=98collateralized=E2=80=99 but not=
 necessarily =E2=80=98overcollateralized=E2=80=99.=E2=80=9D However, the fa=
lse statement was never corrected.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then the complaint goes through various in=
stances of Gemini doing due diligence on Genesis, getting nervous, and then=
 not doing anything about it. Gemini was=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>lying about=
 conducting fairly thorough due diligence: Gemini had a risk management tea=
m, it periodically assessed Genesis, it got a lot of information and drew c=
orrect and alarming conclusions:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around February 2022, Gemini=E2=80=99s risk ma=
nagement team analyzed Genesis Capital=E2=80=99s financial statements for t=
he third quarter of 2021. They stated that =E2=80=9C[c]ompared with peers a=
nd the overall market, Genesis[] [Capital=E2=80=99s] financials are general=
ly weaker with a high leverage ratio and low liquidity ratio, similar to co=
mpanies with CCC/C rating=E2=80=9D (also known as a =E2=80=9Cjunk=E2=80=9D =
rating). Based on this credit rating, the risk management team projected th=
at in a market downturn, =E2=80=9Ca 50-60% default rate for Genesis [Capita=
l] [wa]s an appropriate assumption, given additional risks in Crypto indust=
ry vs traditional industry.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On or around July 18, 2022, Gemini=E2=80=99s r=
isk management and product teams compiled a slide titled =E2=80=9CGemini Ea=
rn: Risk vs. Reward.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6=C2=A0In this document, Gemini ackno=
wledged: =E2=80=9C[the market risk team] believes Genesis [Capital] financi=
al [sic] is similar to a CCC company, which would be required to pay a 14%+=
 yield in the public debt market. Therefore, lenders would require a ~14% y=
ield to compensate for Genesis [Capital]=E2=80=99s default risk.=E2=80=9D</=
p>
</blockquote>
