</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have a quarter-end balance sheet with t=
he right numbers of assets (more) and liabilities (less), the market won=E2=
=80=99t panic, so you=E2=80=99ll solve your liquidity problem: People will =
keep lending you money. If that balance sheet is somewhat fictitious =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0if the assets are an IOU from yourself to yourself at a below-mark=
et rate =E2=80=94=C2=A0that doesn=E2=80=99t really matter; what you have do=
ne is bought yourself time to dig out from the hole you are in.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This did work! For instance,=C2=A0<em>Gemini=
=C2=A0</em>didn=E2=80=99t pull its customers=E2=80=99 money from Genesis af=
