ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Tasos Vossos reports today</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Achim Wiechert=C2=A0was one of the many expert=
s brought in to mend the broken market for bank capital securities in the a=
ftermath of the financial crisis. He worries it could break again =E2=80=94=
 and he=E2=80=99s on a mission to fix it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The head of external funding at insurance gian=
t=C2=A0Allianz SE=C2=A0is lobbying for one of the most far-reaching overhau=
ls to Europe=E2=80=99s $235 billion market for additional tier 1 bank debt =
since it was created more than a decade ago to prevent a rerun of 2008=E2=
=80=99s taxpayer-led bailouts. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wiechert=E2=80=99s concern is that AT1s, which=
 count as capital, will fail to buffer banks from another crisis. This isn=
=E2=80=99t a flaw of the bonds themselves but of market behavior: Conventio=
n dictates that banks repay the notes at their first call date, whether or =
not it makes economic sense.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And at a time when they really need the capita=
l, in a crisis, lenders would be even more compelled to follow those conven=
tions, swallowing punitive debt costs so they can show it=E2=80=99s busines=
s as usual. He argues that the need to keep up appearances could plunge ban=
ks into trouble. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">His solution is to take the decision on whethe=
r to repay AT1s early out of banks=E2=80=99 hands, and leave it up to marke=
t math. Either a replacement bond can be cheaper than a predetermined level=
 or the bank will be barred automatically from exercising the call option.<=
/p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Intuitively, in my Possibility 1, the bank sho=
uld replace its current AT1 with a new, cheaper one. In my Possibility 2, t=
he bank should=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>replace its current AT1 with a new, m=
ore expensive one: It should just leave the old one outstanding, even if in=
vestors are disappointed. The goal of these securities is to disappoint inv=
estors sometimes. That=E2=80=99s why they work as capital.</p>
